    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1912-07-24T12:36:00-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1912-07-24T12:36:00-05:00" n="1124"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d1124">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">File No. 812.00/4481.</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The <gloss type="from">American Ambassador</gloss> to the
                            <gloss type="to">Secretary of State</gloss>
                    </hi>.</head>
                <opener>
                    <seg rendition="#center">[Telegram.—Paraphrase.]</seg>
                </opener>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">American Embassy</hi>, <lb/>
                            <hi rend="italic">Mexico</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1912-07-24T11:00:00-06:36">
                            <hi rend="italic">July 24, 1912—11 a.m.</hi>
                        </date>
                    </dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>Suspension of constitutional guaranties decided on yesterday. This is practically
                    a declaration of martial law in the States of Sonora, Morelos and Chihuahua, and
                    parts of Durango, Puebla, Tlaxcala and Mexico. The reason given by the
                    Government is the increase of atrocities, violation by rebels of laws of
                    civilized warfare in said States. Commanding general in the zone publicly states
                    that he is unable to deal with the situation, not having strong enough forces.
                    There is a simultaneous revival of rebel activity in both north and south. It
                    may be a movement toward cohesion.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Wilson.</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
    </text>
